'''Club Silvio Pettirossi''', is a [[Paraguay]]an [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in the [[barrio]] of [[Republicano]], in [[Asunción]]. The club was founded March 11, 1926 and plays in the [[Paraguayan Cuarta División|fourth division]] of the Paraguayan league. Their home games are played at the Bernabé Pedrozo stadium. The club's name was chosen in honor of [[Silvio Pettirossi]], a famous Paraguayan airplane pilot and [[aviation]] pioneer.

In 2007 they won the [[Liga Paraguaya: Segunda División|Intermedia]] (Paraguayan second division tournament) and will thus be in the top flight of Paraguayan football in 2008. They have named former Paraguayan star [[Miguel Angel Benitez]] as head coach for the 2008 season.

