'''Dina Gorina''' (also spelled '''Qorina''', born 1 November 1987) is an Azerbaijani group [[rhythmic gymnast]]. She represents her nation at international competitions.
She participated at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in Beijing.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/qo/dina-qorina-1.html |title=Dina Qorina (other name: Dina Gorina) |accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> She also competed at world championships, including at the [[2005 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships|2005]] and [[2009 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |title=29th RHYTHMIC GYMNASTICS WORLD CHAMPIONSHIPS - MIE, JAPAN - SEPTEMBER 7th - 13th 2009 |quote=GORINA Dina |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/00000800000000FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF02 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508084111/http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/00000800000000FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF02 |archive-date=8 May 2016 |publisher=LonginesTiming.com |date=10 September 2009 |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>
