'''Ivivva Athletica''' is a youth brand which was founded by [[Lululemon|lululemon athletica]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mairs|first=Alana|title=Welcome to the Family, ivivva!|url=http://www.lululemon.com/community/blog/welcome-to-the-family-ivivva/|work=lululemon athletica blog|publisher=lululemon athletica |accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> Created by lululemon’s for its younger clientele, ivivva focuses on creating athletic [[Sportswear (activewear)|sportswear]] for active girls ages 6–14.<ref>{{cite web|last=Nezinol|first=Jennifer|title=lululemon athletica inc. introduces ivivva athletica|url=http://investor.lululemon.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=406278&sli=1|work=Investor Relations|publisher=lululemon athletica|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> The company launched with its first store in [[Vancouver|Vancouver, Canada]] in December 2009, and has since grown to over 70 stores and [[pop-up shop]] locations across Canada and the United States.<ref>{{cite web|last=athletica|first=ivivva|title=ivivva locations|url=http://www.ivivva.com/about-ivivva/stores/|work=ivivva athletica website|publisher=ivivva athletica |accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> In 2012 ivivva opened its first American stores in [[New York City|New York]], [[Chicago]], [[Boston]], [[Bellevue, Washington|Bellevue]] and [[Orange County, California|Orange County]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Gerstenblatt|first=Julie|title=Lululemon for Girls?! Yes, it's True! Meet Ivivva|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/julie-gerstenblatt/lululemon_b_2006375.html|accessdate=21 January 2013|newspaper=Huffington Post|date=October 23, 2012}}</ref> ivivva’s clothes are designed for young girls in a wide variety of athletic pursuits such as dance, running, yoga, ice skating, gymnastics and on-the-court sports. The majority of their clothing line is heavily influenced by direct input from customers to ensure quality, fit, and function.<ref>{{cite web|last=Athletica|first=Ivivva|title=Help Us Design|url=http://www.ivivva.com/product-info/help-us-design/|work=ivivva athletica website|publisher=ivivva athletica website|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref>
In June 2017, Lululemon Athletica announced the closures of Ivivva stores and focusing the Ivivva brand [[Online shopping|online]].
