{{Original research|date=June 2011}}
'''Kbach kun dambong veng''' ({{lang-km|ក្បាច់គុណដំបងវែង}}) is the term for a [[Cambodia]]n martial art based on the long staff.  The term "dambong" means "staff" in the [[Khmer language]] and the term "veng" means "long".  Translated literally it means "the art/martial skill of the long staff." The term is also used in the phrase "land of the lost staff", [[Battambang]].  In the town of Battambang there is a big statue of 'Grandfather Dambong' holding the lost staff. It is based on different mae(s) which can be imagined as a Khmer version of [[kata]](s).[[File:Knee and staff.png|thumb|Knee and staff]][[File:Naktadambangkragnoung.jpg|thumb|right|200px| A statue of Grandfather Dambong carrying a long staff.]]

