'''Palandöken Ice Skating Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Palandöken Buz Pateni Salonu}}), formerly '''GSIM Yenişehir Ice Hockey Hall''' ({{lang-tr|GSİM Yenişehir Buz Hokey Salonu}}) or '''Erzurum Ice Skating Hall''' ({{lang-tr|Erzurum Buz Pateni Salonu}}), is an indoor [[ice skating]] and [[ice hockey]] [[ice rink|rink]] located at Ahmet Baba neighborhood of [[Palandöken, Erzurum|Palandöken]] district in [[Erzurum]], eastern [[Turkey]].<ref name="tbhf1"/> It was opened in 2008.<ref name="gsb"/>
Owned by the Youth and Sport Directorate of Erzurum Province (GSIM), the venue has a [[seating capacity]] of 2,000 spectators.<ref name="gsb"/> The rink hosts also [[figure skating]] and [[short track speed skating]] events in addition to ice hockey games.<ref name="eh1"/><ref name="eo1"/>
