The '''Romanian Gymnastics Federation''' (RGF) is the governing body of [[gymnastics]] in [[Romania]]. Established in 1906, it supervises gymnastics clubs and gymnasts' participation in international competitions.<ref>''[https://books.google.com/books?id=mYBtMajLAaAC&printsec=frontcover Sports Around the World]''. 2012. p. 331.</ref>

Adrian Stoica was re-elected president of the RGF in 2013.<ref>[http://www.ueg.org/en/Romanian-Gymnastics-Federation-elections-2013-03-13-0000 "Romanian Gymnastics Federation: elections"]. ueg.org. March 13, 2013. Retrieved May 11, 2013.</ref>

