The '''Stade Alphonse Massemba-Débat''' (formally named '''Stade de la Revolution''') in [[Brazzaville]] is the [[national stadium]] of the [[Republic of the Congo]]. It is used for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and also has an [[athletics (sport)|athletics]] track and a [[team handball|handball]] court. It hosts the home games of [[CARA Brazzaville]] and [[Etoile du Congo]]. It holds 33,037 people. It was the venue for the [[1965 All-Africa Games]] and the [[2004 African Championships in Athletics]].

